<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-10-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-10-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="331" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d331">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to
                                    <persName type="to">Baron Fava</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-10-10"><hi rend="italic">October 10,
                                1896</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 161.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your note of the 27th ultimo relative to the lynching at
                            Hahnville in response to Department’s note No. 155, of the 21st ultimo,
                            on the same subject.</p>
                        <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Richard Olney.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>